# Template Files

## Required Files
- `style.css` with proper theme header (Theme Name, Version, etc.)
- `index.php` as fallback template
- `functions.php` for theme setup

## Template Structure
- Use The Loop properly for displaying posts
- Check if posts exist: `if (have_posts()) : while (have_posts()) : the_post();`
- Use `get_header()`, `get_footer()`, `get_sidebar()` for template parts
- Use `get_template_part()` for reusable components

## Best Practices
- Never hardcode URLs - use `home_url()`, `get_template_directory_uri()`
- Don't include jQuery from CDN - use WordPress bundled version
- Make all strings translatable with `__()`, `_e()`, `esc_html__()`
- Don't use inline styles or scripts - enqueue them properly
- Provide fallback content when no posts exist
- Use WordPress template tags over raw PHP when available

## Child Themes
- Child themes need only `style.css` with `Template:` header pointing to parent
- Enqueue parent styles in child functions.php
- Override only necessary templates from parent theme
